(44, 18, 25, 7, 2, 22, 22, 'the way of the Lord', 'Connection of Keeping the Way', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of ''the way of the Lord.'' Acts 18:25 highlights the fervent teaching of this way, while Judges 2:22 focuses on proving Israel''s commitment to it.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 26, 44, 14, 3, 3, NULL, 'Boldness in Speaking for God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of boldness in proclaiming the message of God. In Acts 18:26, Aquila and Priscilla hear someone speaking boldly, while in Acts 14:3, the apostles are described as speaking boldly in the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 26, 44, 18, 25, 25, 'the way of God more perfectly', 'Connection of Instruction and Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the teaching of the way of God. Acts 18:25 describes Apollos as instructed in the way of the Lord, while Acts 18:26 shows Aquila and Priscilla expounding this way more perfectly.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 26, 46, 12, 21, 21, 'expounded unto him the way of God', 'Unity in the Body of Christ', 'This connection highlights the importance of mutual support and teaching within the Christian community. Both passages emphasize the necessity of every member''s contribution, as seen in Aquila and Priscilla''s guidance of Apollos and the interdependence described in the body of Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 26, 49, 6, 19, 20, 'speak boldly', 'Boldness in Speaking', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of speaking boldly about the gospel. In Acts, Aquila and Priscilla help Apollos to speak more perfectly, while in Ephesians, Paul requests boldness to proclaim the mystery of the gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 26, 58, 6, 1, 1, 'way of God more perfectly', 'Pursuit of Spiritual Maturity', 'This connection highlights the theme of progressing towards perfection in faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of deepening one''s understanding of God''s ways and moving beyond foundational teachings.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 26, 20, 1, 5, 5, 'expounded unto him the way of God', 'Wisdom and Learning Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of increasing knowledge and understanding. In Acts, Aquila and Priscilla help Apollos to ''expound'' the way of God, paralleling Proverbs'' emphasis on a wise man who ''will hear'' and ''increase learning.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 26, 20, 9, 9, 9, 'expounded unto him the way of God', 'Wisdom and Instruction', 'This connection highlights the theme of teaching and learning. In Acts, Aquila and Priscilla instruct Apollos, paralleling Proverbs'' emphasis on giving instruction to wise individuals to increase their understanding.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 27, 53, 2, 13, 14, 'believed through grace', 'Connection of Grace and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief through grace. In Acts, believers are helped through grace, while in 2 Thessalonians, salvation is linked to belief of the truth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 27, 59, 1, 16, 18, 'believed through grace', 'Connection of Grace and Gifts', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace as a gift from God. In Acts, believers are helped through grace, while James emphasizes that every good gift comes from the Father.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 27, 43, 1, 12, 13, NULL, 'Connection of Belief and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the act of receiving and believing. In Acts, those who received him were helped in their belief through grace, while in John, receiving Him grants the power to become sons of God through belief.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 27, 44, 9, 27, 27, 'helped them much which had believed', 'Support for New Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the role of support in the faith journey. In Acts 18:27, the brethren encourage the disciples to receive him, paralleling how Barnabas advocates for Saul in Acts 9:27.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 27, 44, 18, 18, 18, 'helped them much which had believed', 'Connection of Paul and Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Paul in supporting fellow believers. In Acts 18:27, Paul is received by the disciples, while in Acts 18:18, he departs with Priscilla and Aquila, indicating a collaborative ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 27, 45, 1, 5, 5, 'believed through grace', 'Connection of Grace and Apostleship', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace in both passages. Acts 18:27 mentions those who ''believed through grace,'' while Romans 1:5 speaks of receiving grace for the purpose of faith among all nations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 27, 45, 16, 1, 2, NULL, 'Support and Reception of Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving and assisting fellow believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of supporting those who have helped others in faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 28, 44, 18, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Testimony to Jews', 'Both passages emphasize the act of testifying to the Jews that Jesus was Christ. This connection highlights the continuity of Paul''s mission in proclaiming Jesus'' identity.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 28, 46, 15, 3, 4, 'that Jesus was Christ', 'Connection of Christ''s Identity', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus as the Christ, as both passages affirm His identity through the scriptures. Acts 18:28 emphasizes convincing the Jews that Jesus was Christ, while 1 Corinthians 15:3-4 states that Christ''s death and resurrection occurred according to the scriptures.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 28, 44, 9, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Convincing Arguments', 'Both passages emphasize the act of convincing the Jews by proving Jesus as the Christ. This connection highlights the shared theme of using scripture to affirm Jesus'' identity.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 28, 42, 24, 44, 44, 'shewing by the scriptures that Jesus was Christ', 'Connection of Scripture Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus being the fulfillment of the scriptures. Both passages emphasize the necessity of understanding the scriptures in relation to Jesus as the Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 28, 42, 24, 27, 27, 'shewing by the scriptures that Jesus was Christ', 'Connection of Scriptural Conviction', 'Both passages emphasize the use of scriptures to reveal Jesus as the Christ. Acts 18:28 shows a public demonstration of this truth, while Luke 24:27 illustrates Jesus expounding the scriptures concerning himself.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 28, 43, 5, 39, 39, 'shewing by the scriptures that Jesus was Christ', 'Connection of Scriptures Testifying', 'Both passages emphasize the role of scriptures in revealing Jesus as the Christ. Acts 18:28 shows that the scriptures were used to convince others of Jesus'' identity, while John 5:39 states that the scriptures testify of Him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 18, 28, 58, 7, 1, 10, 'Jesus was Christ', 'Connection of Jesus and Melchisedec', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of priesthood, with Acts highlighting Jesus as the Christ and Hebrews presenting Melchisedec as a priest. This connection illustrates the continuity of God''s plan through different priestly figures.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
